% You are an expert Python engineer. Your goal is to write the CLI commands module `pdd/commands/maintenance.py`, which defines three Click commands: `sync`, `auto_deps`, and `setup`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Role & Scope
  This module defines three Click commands for PDD maintenance operations
  (sync, auto-deps, setup). Each command delegates to an internal "main"
  function. `sync` and `auto_deps` are decorated with `@track_cost` and
  return `Optional[Tuple[str, float, str]]` (result, cost, model_name) on
  success, or None on failure.

% Dependencies
  <maintenance_example>
    <include>context/commands/maintenance_example.py</include>
  </maintenance_example>

% Requirements

  1. `sync` command:
     - Argument: BASENAME (required str) — prompt basename or GitHub issue URL.
     - Options: --max-attempts (int), --budget (float), --skip-verify (flag),
       --skip-tests (flag), --target-coverage (float), --dry-run (flag),
       --log (hidden deprecated flag), --no-steer (flag), --steer-timeout (float),
       --agentic (flag), --timeout-adder (float, default 0.0),
       --no-github-state (flag), --one-session/--no-one-session (default None).
     - All option defaults are None or False; downstream functions apply .pddrc values.
     - Decorated with `@track_cost` (applied below `@click.pass_context`).
     - Deprecated --log: emit yellow warning to stderr, set dry_run=True.
     - GitHub issue URL dispatch: if `_is_github_issue_url(basename)` is true,
       delegate to `_run_agentic_sync_dispatch` helper. Default one_session=True
       for agentic sync, False for single-module sync.
     - Single-module path: call `sync_main(...)`, return `(str(result), total_cost, model_name)`.
     - Error handling: re-raise `click.Abort`; catch all others via `handle_error`.

  2. `_run_agentic_sync_dispatch` helper function:
     - Extracts quiet/verbose from ctx.obj, calls `run_agentic_sync(...)`.
     - Prints status/message/cost/model unless quiet.
     - On failure: raise `click.exceptions.Exit(1)`.
     - Re-raises click.Abort and click.exceptions.Exit; catches others via handle_error.

  3. `auto_deps` command (name="auto-deps"):
     - Arguments: PROMPT_FILE (exists=True, dir_okay=False) and DIRECTORY_PATH
       (exists=False, file_okay=False — allows quoted paths or unexpanded globs).
     - Options: --output (writable path), --csv (writable path), --force-scan (flag).
     - Decorated with `@track_cost`.
     - Strip quotes from directory_path before passing to `auto_deps_main`.
     - Delegates to `auto_deps_main(ctx, prompt_file, directory_path, auto_deps_csv_path=csv, output, force_scan)`.

  4. `setup` command:
     - No arguments or options. Decorated with `@click.pass_context` only (no @track_cost).
     - Lazily imports `cli` module (`from .. import cli as cli_module`) inside the
       function body for testability.
     - Handles ctx.obj being None gracefully (quiet defaults to False).
     - First calls `cli_module.install_completion(quiet=quiet)`, then `_run_setup_utility()`.

% Deliverables
  - Code: `pdd/commands/maintenance.py`
